Opposition blames Syrian and Lebanese governments for Hariri's assassination
Opposition leaders on Monday held Lebanese and Syrian governments responsiblefor the assassination of former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri, demanded Syriantroops withdraw from Lebanon within the next three months and called on theinternational community to intervene to help "this captive nation."
